verbose_text: We found that ced-3 and ced-4 mutations, which eliminate apoptotic cell death, led to a significant change to the germline profiles of day 1 sterile prg-1 mutant adults (XREF_SUPPLEMENTARY), and overall reduced levels of germline atrophy, as did deficiency for nhr-49 (XREF_FIG).
evidence: ced-3 and ced-4 mutations, which eliminate apoptotic cell death
